Humm, I think I know, I've been able to reproduce and placed some traces, and it seems can have both `window->on_all_workspaces=1` and `window->workspace != NULL`.

However, in `set_workspace_state()` we check for `window->workspace` first and won't remove the window from all workspaces in `window->workspace` is not NULL:

```
4692   if (window->workspace)
4693     meta_workspace_remove_window (window->workspace, window);
4694   else if (window->on_all_workspaces)
4695     {
4696       GList *l;
4697       for (l = window->screen->workspaces; l != NULL; l = l->next)
4698         {
4699           MetaWorkspace *ws = l->data;
4700           meta_workspace_remove_window (ws, window);
4701         }
4702     }
```

Therefore, if `window->workspace != NULL` we won't remove the window from other workspaces, which triggers the g_assert() we hit later.

